# 2 Logistic Regression

Fig 1. Full model workflow with split, fit, predict, and evaluate process steps

2.1 Setup Data

# setup model data
d <- pts_env %>% 
  select(-ID) %>%  # remove terms we don't want to model
  tidyr::drop_na() # drop the rows with NA values
nrow(d)
## [1] 4440

2.2 Linear Model

# fit a linear model
mdl <- lm(present ~ ., data = d)
summary(mdl)
##

## lm(formula = present ~ ., data = d)
##

2.3 Generalized Linear Model (GLM)

  • see https://www.statmethods.net/advstats/glm.html for help
# fit a generalized linear model with a binomial logit link function
mdl <- glm(present ~ ., family = binomial(link="logit"), data = d)
summary(mdl)
## 
## Call:
## glm(formula = present ~ ., family = binomial(link = "logit"),
